`viz/` is a single-file static frontend for inspecting the compiled steno
stroke tree, consumed only by a human running it in a browser against a
locally generated `../out/viz-data.json`; it has no other contract with
the rest of the codebase beyond that JSON shape and must be served over
`http://`.

The whole subtree is `index.html.ctx` — one file, so there's no
cross-file coupling within `viz/` itself. The coupling that matters is
external: the bank layout constants and stroke parser here are a hand
maintained copy of `crates/steno/src/stroke/keys.rs`, and the one-liner
toggle semantics mirror `lineflag.rs`. Any change to canonical stroke
layout, parsing, or one-liner/multi-line selection rules in the Rust
crate requires a matching edit here, with nothing to enforce that
automatically.

